        Media captionThe SNP's Ian Blackford says the Brexit deal denies Scottish rightsMeanwhile, Northern Ireland's Democratic Unionist Party, which keeps Mrs May's in power, has said it would support the government in a confidence motion if the deal was thrown out on Tuesday.
    
        
            
                
                    
